[recto] Ad [Addendum] 50. Witt Library. Quarrel at Cards: 1) Comte Cavens Coll. (Rubens); 2) Vienna - blurred photo; 3) Dresden, N° 819, Photo Bruckmann 1901, in landscape; 4) Very poor (by P.B.II?) Riabouchinsky Sale, New York, 26-IV-1916, N° 12, Panel 16 x 22 cm; 5) Old Photograph of version similar to 4, certainly by the same hand (=P.B.II?); 6) Private Coll; Tournai; [verso] 7) Henri Rouart Sale, Paris 1912, Planche (or Cat.) N° 4, better version similar to Dresden; 8) Vienna, Gemälde Galerie, N° 728 as Lucas van Valckenborch: Bauern schlägerei, Photo Bruckmann 1903 (in Witt Library under Valckenborch); c) Sebastien Vranckx, Sale Giroux, Brussels, 10 March 1930, N° 48 La Rixe, Bois 36,5 x 46 cm (Pl. XXII). In Witt Library under Vrancx Miscellaneous, similar outdoor. Like the Rubens version, but without chicken.
